I want to say that today has been a very emotional/stressful day but I still walked across that stage with my head held high with my angel by my side.!These past couple of months I been so excited but nervous at the same time for this day to come but along the way I lost someone who meant the world to me 4 months before graduation but I still held on and went strong because I know that’s what my uncle would’ve wanted! I know your looking down on me so proud and I’m happy that I made you proud! It was a very long journey but so worth it  I used to say “we doing all these years of school just for a piece of paper” but a lot comes with getting it and I’m so proud of myself for getting through it and not letting negativity or pain stand in the way! Some Advice for  anyone still in school don’t give up no matter what you think is “to hard “ “to much” you got this if I can do it you can! Thanks everybody who made it and thank you to everyone that congratulated me! I’m on to a new chapter in life this is where it all begins I hope you all will also be along the journey!  Thank you so much to my mom Ebonies Kitchen for showing me just how strong I could be in all areas and giving birth to me lol cause I wouldn’t be here without her 🫶🏽 (her first graduate)  thanks to my dad @bernardshoni-mac Shaw for also showing me how strong I am! And giving me my talents lol my momma too but she can’t sing for nothing 😂. Thank you to my unclePharaoh Rell (HELL RELL ) for teaching me a love I’ll forever know and for teaching me how to heal without your presence it’s hard but I got this 🕊️, Thank you to my God MomEve Brown for being there for me at my TOUGHEST,craziest, emotional moments , Thank you stink Lul Nita for being the most help this whole high school year lol  I love you thanks for everything! and everyone else I didn’t mention thank you for believing in me! I LOVE YALL! Class of 2023 we did it !🫶🏽❤️🕊️ #classof2023 #ididitformyuncle #RNnurse #highschoolgraduation #firstgraduate @upstrz
